==English==
===Etymology===
Hindustani '''[[मसाला]]''' / '''{{URchar|[[مسالا]]}}'''  (masālā) "spice(s)", from Persian '''{{FAchar|[[مصالح]]}}''' (maṣālih) "affairs, materials, spices", plural of '''{{FAchar|[[مصلحت]]}}''' (maṣlahat) "affair, policy, best thing to do", both from Arabic, derived from '''{{ARchar|[[صلح]]}}''' (ṣálaḥa) "be fit, competent, usable".

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːlə|-ɑːlə]]

